### Describe the bug

A serialized VoidTaskResult is written to the _HttpResponse.Body_ when an endpoint filter is used and the endpoint fails argument validation.

**Reason behind the issue**
The reasons this occurs is because the pipeline will return a _ValueTask.FromResult\<object\>(Task.CompletedTask)_ when the HttpContext.Response.StatusCode is 400 as seen below, this will then be serialized to Json when _AddResponseWritingToMethodCall_ detects that the return type is _ValueTask\<object\>_ and call the method chain _ExecuteValueTaskOfObject_ > _ExecuteAwaitedReturn_ > _WriteJsonResponse_

```C#
var filteredInvocation = Expression.Lambda<EndpointFilterDelegate>(
            Expression.Condition(
                Expression.GreaterThanOrEqual(FilterContextHttpContextStatusCodeExpr, Expression.Constant(400)),
                CompletedValueTaskExpr,
                handlerInvocation),
            FilterContextExpr).Compile();
```

An existing unit test (_RequestDelegateFactory_InvokesFiltersButNotHandler_OnArgumentError_) would catch this issue if it checked that the _HttpContext.Response.Body_ should be empty at the end of the test.

**Possible solution**
The easiest solution I have found is just to check if the value in _ExecuteAwaitedReturn_ is of type Task.Completed as seen in the last else if statement below, and skip the JSON serialization.

Thoughts?

```C#
private static Task ExecuteAwaitedReturn(object obj, HttpContext httpContext)
{
    // Terminal built ins
    if (obj is IResult result)
    {
        return ExecuteResultWriteResponse(result, httpContext);
    }
    else if (obj is string stringValue)
    {
        SetPlaintextContentType(httpContext);
        return httpContext.Response.WriteAsync(stringValue);
    }
    else if (obj != Task.CompletedTask)
    {
        // Otherwise, we JSON serialize when we reach the terminal state
        return WriteJsonResponse(httpContext.Response, obj);
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
}
```

### Expected Behavior

I would expect to get a 400 status code without a response body, this is the behavior you get when no endpoint filter is defined.

